1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:11,533
<i> That's enough!</i>

2
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:13,333
<i>Why are you flirting
with my fiancé?</i>

3
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:15,367
<i> Face me!</i>

4
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:17,333
<i> Go and like someone else.</i>

5
00:00:17,467 --> 00:00:20,133
<i>I don't care even if I like you.</i>

6
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:22,200
<i>Because the old Mookie
will never return.</i>

7
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,267
<i> You like me, too?</i>

8
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,100
<i>Why don't you want
to show me your face?</i>

9
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:26,967
<i> Emma?</i>

10
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,300
<i> Isn't that our plan B?</i>

11
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>Marie will come to the rescue
if everything gets tough.</i>

12
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:34,167
<i>Stop fooling me.
I know you're Emma!</i>

13
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:36,967
<i>I won't allow us to be
anything less than okay.</i>

14
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:37,733
<i> Let's go!</i>

15
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:38,500
<i> Emma!</i>

16
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:39,467
<i> Even just for your daughter.</i>

17
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,633
<i> Do you think she'll come back?</i>

18
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:42,133
<i> She's gone forever!</i>

19
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:44,433
<i> She left you for another man!</i>

20
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:46,800
<i>She loves someone else now.
And that's not you.</i>

21
00:00:46,933 --> 00:00:51,367
<i>Promise me that we will never
talk about Emma ever again.</i>

22
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,333
<i> Please.</i>

23
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:53,767
<i> Tell me the truth.</i>

24
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:55,633
<i> Do you still love Danilo?</i>

25
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:33,567
Do you still love Danilo?

26
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:37,333
Why are you asking me that?

27
00:01:37,467 --> 00:01:40,567
And why are you raising
your voice on me?

28
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:49,500
Nothing.

29
00:01:54,167 --> 00:01:56,233
I'm sorry.

30
00:01:56,367 --> 00:01:58,433
I'm sorry.

31
00:01:58,567 --> 00:02:01,600
I'm just worried.

32
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:02,600
Emma...

33
00:02:05,267 --> 00:02:07,500
let me remind you.

34
00:02:07,633 --> 00:02:09,900
We're in the middle
of the fight.

35
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:12,933
I need to know
all the weaknesses

36
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:15,733
that can ruin your defense.

37
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:20,767
If you love Danilo,
all our plains will fail.

38
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:23,533
Everything we prepared
for will go to waste.

39
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,067
I don't care about Danilo.

40
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:34,700
All I want to take back
from Jade is Mookie.

41
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:39,800
Logan, just Mookie.

42
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:40,900
Good.

43
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,000
That's all I want to hear.

44
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:49,367
Thank you, Emma.

45
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:59,300
Why the long face?

46
00:02:59,433 --> 00:03:00,667
Are you crying?

47
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,967
No, I'm just happy.

48
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:05,867
Even though our plan
almost got ruined,

49
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,367
we successfully executed it.

50
00:03:10,133 --> 00:03:16,467
It feels good to see Jade
crumbling like a wall...

51
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:22,200
losing herself,
confused, and speechless.

52
00:03:25,867 --> 00:03:27,933
We've only started, Emma.

53
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:33,100
Are you ready
for your next move?

54
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:03,033
Loida, please call Mookie
if everything is ready.

55
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:07,000
Hello?

56
00:04:07,133 --> 00:04:09,533
Danilo left early.

57
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:11,067
He didn't tell me where he went.

58
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,867
Stop being paranoid.
Haven't you reconciled already?

59
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,767
That's not the point.

60
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,100
I just have a bad feeling
about this.

61
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:20,600
Danilo has been acting
differently after the launch.

62
00:04:20,733 --> 00:04:24,667
I think he's looking for Emma.

63
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:28,967
Why don't you tell him that
Emma's dead so that he'll stop?

64
00:04:29,133 --> 00:04:30,333
No!

65
00:04:30,467 --> 00:04:32,767
My husband and daughter
will grieve.

66
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:35,633
And Emma will be the star again.
I'll be left out again.

67
00:04:35,767 --> 00:04:36,800
No way.

68
00:04:36,933 --> 00:04:41,333
Besides, how will I explain
the picture, Leticia?

69
00:04:41,467 --> 00:04:43,633
What if Danilo has
it investigated?

70
00:04:43,767 --> 00:04:45,700
You should calm down.

71
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:47,967
Let's do something
to relax later.

72
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:52,633
I'll hang up now. See you in the
office. I saw a cutie here.

73
00:04:52,767 --> 00:04:53,767
Bye.

74
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,233
See you.

75
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:52,900
Hello, Leticia.

76
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:58,033
Hello?

77
00:05:58,167 --> 00:05:59,367
Leticia.

78
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:04,633
Hello, Leticia.
Why don't you say anything?

79
00:06:04,767 --> 00:06:06,100
Hi, Sis.

80
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:07,467
How are you?

81
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:12,633
Emma?

82
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,633
How nice it is for you
to remember my voice.

83
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:19,767
I'm calling from the grave.

84
00:06:23,467 --> 00:06:25,300
Leticia, this is not funny.

85
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:28,800
Stop this prank call
because it's not funny.

86
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:31,533
Who's Leticia?

87
00:06:31,667 --> 00:06:33,200
I said stop it!

88
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,667
Stop, Leticia!

89
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,833
I'm warning you!

90
00:06:36,967 --> 00:06:40,033
Will you also kill her
like what you did to me, Sis?

91
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:46,900
How are Danilo and Mookie?

92
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:50,700
How are my husband and daughter
that you stole from me?

93
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:52,233
No.

94
00:06:52,367 --> 00:06:53,100
No.

95
00:06:53,233 --> 00:06:54,133
No.

96
00:06:54,267 --> 00:06:55,300
No, no.

97
00:06:55,433 --> 00:06:57,333
You're not real.

98
00:06:57,467 --> 00:06:59,033
You're dead, Emma.

99
00:06:59,167 --> 00:06:59,967
You're dead.

100
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:02,733
This is impossible!

101
00:07:02,867 --> 00:07:04,500
Because you killed me.

102
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:12,100
No!

103
00:07:12,233 --> 00:07:13,533
Am I hallucinating?

104
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,467
I'm only imagining things.

105
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,233
This is not real.

106
00:07:35,367 --> 00:07:36,400
Oh my God!

107
00:07:36,533 --> 00:07:37,633
She's dead!

108
00:07:37,767 --> 00:07:38,833
No!

109
00:07:38,967 --> 00:07:40,033
No!

110
00:07:40,167 --> 00:07:41,400
Hello, Jade?

111
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:42,567
No!

112
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,833
Leave me alone! You're dead!

113
00:07:44,967 --> 00:07:46,567
I know you're dead!

114
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:49,467
- No! No!
- Aunt Jade.

115
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:50,700
- Mookie.
- Jade, what's happening?

116
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:52,000
Keep that away from me!

117
00:07:52,133 --> 00:07:53,400
- Don't touch that!
- Aunt Leticia?

118
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:54,667
Mookie.

119
00:08:03,433 --> 00:08:04,500
What's happening?

120
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:06,333
Auntie, what's going on?

121
00:08:06,467 --> 00:08:08,100
Put that down, Mookie!

122
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:09,167
No!

123
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:10,400
Auntie...

124
00:08:10,533 --> 00:08:12,433
No! Keep that away from me!

125
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:13,500
No!

126
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:14,300
No!

127
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:19,100
Jade, can you please
stop pranking Mookie?

128
00:08:19,233 --> 00:08:20,700
The kid is getting scared.

129
00:08:33,567 --> 00:08:34,500
Leticia?

130
00:08:37,233 --> 00:08:39,300
Yeah.

131
00:08:39,433 --> 00:08:40,900
You're so silly.

132
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:43,433
Don't ever pull
that prank again.

133
00:08:43,567 --> 00:08:46,800
Bye. I'll see you at the office.

134
00:08:46,933 --> 00:08:48,667
Okay, okay.

135
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,333
What the hell?

136
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,733
Are you okay, Aunt Jade?

137
00:08:56,900 --> 00:09:00,100
I'm so sorry, Mookie,
that I scared you.

138
00:09:00,233 --> 00:09:01,400
It's Leticia's fault.

139
00:09:01,533 --> 00:09:02,433
It's just...

140
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:05,000
it's an old prank that
she's been pulling since

141
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:07,067
we were younger.

142
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,400
I'm so sorry.

143
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,700
Are you ready to eat?

144
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:13,567
Wait for me there, sweetie.

145
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,833
I'll have the food
brought there.

146
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,233
I'll just change my clothes.

147
00:09:16,367 --> 00:09:17,667
I'll see you there.

148
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:49,067
I'll get back to you.

149
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:12,233
Tell me the truth.

150
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:14,467
Are you working with Emma?

151
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,667
What?

152
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:16,933
Are you serious?

153
00:10:17,067 --> 00:10:19,200
Then explain to me that call.

154
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:21,433
I don't know.

155
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:23,067
Maybe I tapped the button.

156
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,900
You were my last call.

157
00:10:26,033 --> 00:10:28,800
Jade, I'm getting worried
about you.

158
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:30,633
It was your second time.

159
00:10:30,767 --> 00:10:33,100
You're hallucinating again.

160
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:34,400
So, please.

161
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:35,667
Take your medicines already.

162
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,267
No!

163
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:40,233
It's been a long time
since I last took Pryvaxil.

164
00:10:40,367 --> 00:10:43,067
I haven't had episodes
like this in a while.

165
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:47,133
You know what?

166
00:10:47,267 --> 00:10:50,433
Maybe I'm only getting
stressed because of Emma.

167
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:52,467
But I shouldn't.

168
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:56,467
Because I won't let a dead
person defeat me.

169
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,867
Take this just in case.

170
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,067
Please.

171
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:06,367
Fine.

172
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:07,600
Let's go.

173
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:24,700
You know what, Olive?

174
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:27,633
Emma is the only cause
of your stress.

175
00:11:27,767 --> 00:11:31,000
Why not focus on other things?

176
00:11:31,133 --> 00:11:36,333
Happy things like your wedding
with Danilo.

177
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:38,033
Oh, yes.

178
00:11:38,167 --> 00:11:39,500
My wedding.

179
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,767
Do you know what my dream
wedding is?

180
00:11:43,933 --> 00:11:46,767
The backdrop is a waterfall,

181
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:50,567
which symbolizes the abundant
flow of water.

182
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:53,267
It's like the abundant flow

183
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:55,833
of Danilo and Mookie's
love for me.

184
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:59,400
That sounds nice.

185
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:04,067
But I wish you would also
think about your mental health

186
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,800
for your life-long happiness.

187
00:12:06,933 --> 00:12:08,167
So, please.

188
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:09,767
Take your meds.

189
00:12:10,867 --> 00:12:12,567
Leticia, listen.

190
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:17,200
Danilo and Mookie are my meds.

191
00:12:18,967 --> 00:12:20,133
Thank you.

192
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:24,833
Oh, yes. I will stay
for a few more minutes.

193
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:29,433
As for me, I'll check their
other services.

194
00:12:29,567 --> 00:12:31,167
I need a manicure.

195
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:33,467
- See you later.
- See you later.

196
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:07,833
<i>Syndicates and criminals use
Necrosol</i>

197
00:13:07,967 --> 00:13:10,967
<i>to make their victims
fall asleep fast.</i>

198
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:14,733
<i>Anyone who takes this will fall
unconscious after a minute.</i>

199
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:21,800
Ma'am, your tea is here.

200
00:13:24,533 --> 00:13:25,667
Thank you.

201
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:37,067
Thank you.

202
00:13:46,133 --> 00:13:47,633
This is good.

203
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,333
What tea is this?

204
00:13:55,233 --> 00:13:56,367
Hi, Sis.

205
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,700
Did you miss me?

206
00:14:02,867 --> 00:14:03,533
Emma?

207
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,500
Hi, Sis.

208
00:14:11,633 --> 00:14:13,600
Did you miss me?

209
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:14,500
No.

210
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:17,033
No.

211
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,467
No.

212
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,100
This can't be.

213
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,233
Emma.

214
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:23,567
Stop it.

215
00:14:24,533 --> 00:14:25,600
You're not real.

216
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,533
I'm only imagining this.

217
00:14:29,667 --> 00:14:31,233
This is just my imagination.

218
00:14:31,367 --> 00:14:32,367
You're not real.

219
00:14:33,833 --> 00:14:35,400
You're not real.

220
00:14:35,533 --> 00:14:36,733
You're dead.

221
00:14:36,867 --> 00:14:39,167
I'm sure you're dead.

222
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,233
No!

223
00:14:51,167 --> 00:14:53,233
Mooks, sorry.

224
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:54,533
You didn't make it.

225
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:57,867
But for sure, Stacy rigged
the tryout results.

226
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,600
It's okay.

227
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:02,433
I don't want to be
a cheerleader, anyway.

228
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,667
Sorry, Mooks.

229
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,200
My class got finished late.

230
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,267
Let's go.

231
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:11,533
Why are you holding
each other's hands?

232
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:15,533
You, two.

233
00:15:18,767 --> 00:15:20,200
Oh, she's so thrilled.

234
00:15:25,033 --> 00:15:26,200
Hi, Mookie.

235
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,267
<i> Stop it!</i>

236
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:40,567
<i> Hey!</i>

237
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:41,700
<i> Leave Zayn alone!</i>

238
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:42,933
<i> Stop!</i>

239
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:46,733
Zayn.

240
00:15:48,367 --> 00:15:49,633
I was right.

241
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,900
That was them.

242
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:54,833
Look at his shoes.

243
00:15:54,967 --> 00:15:56,100
What do you mean?

244
00:15:59,267 --> 00:16:02,167
They're the ones who attacked
Mookie and beat me.

245
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:03,300
What?

246
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:06,900
Zayn!

247
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:10,767
Come here!

248
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:11,600
Zayn!

249
00:16:11,733 --> 00:16:12,200
Zayn!

250
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:12,933
What's your problem?

251
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:14,100
Let me go!

252
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:16,200
Did Stacy order you to do that?

253
00:16:16,333 --> 00:16:17,233
Answer me!

254
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:30,033
Let's go, Zayn!
Let's just forget what happened!

255
00:16:30,167 --> 00:16:30,567
Let's go!

256
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:31,600
No, Mooks.

257
00:16:31,733 --> 00:16:33,467
I wouldn't mind
if it was just me.

258
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,800
I can fight all day, all night.

259
00:16:35,933 --> 00:16:37,933
But I won't let them hurt you,
too.

260
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,200
Zayn, chill.

261
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:41,500
I'm sorry.

262
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:43,733
Mookie, I'm sorry.

263
00:16:43,867 --> 00:16:45,300
So you're admitting it?

264
00:16:45,433 --> 00:16:47,000
You were the ones who attacked
Mookie?

265
00:16:48,467 --> 00:16:49,500
Who told you to do that?

266
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:50,967
It was Stacy, right?

267
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,400
Did Stacy tell you to do that?

268
00:16:53,767 --> 00:16:54,700
What?

269
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:57,933
Yes.

270
00:16:59,533 --> 00:17:01,267
Stacy wanted to get even
with Mookie.

271
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:09,700
Stacy!

272
00:17:12,633 --> 00:17:14,700
I'm warning you.

273
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:18,333
You'll regret it if you hurt
my girlfriend again.

274
00:17:19,433 --> 00:17:20,933
Oh my God.

275
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:22,733
So, are you two together?

276
00:17:22,867 --> 00:17:24,633
Please, Cacai.
Save that for later.

277
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:26,033
Again, Stacy.

278
00:17:26,167 --> 00:17:27,900
Leave her alone.

279
00:17:41,567 --> 00:17:42,700
Are you okay?

280
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,133
Yes, Cacai.

281
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:52,400
We're in a relationship.

282
00:17:52,533 --> 00:17:53,733
I knew it.

283
00:17:53,867 --> 00:17:55,500
That's why you're so sweet
with each other.

284
00:17:55,633 --> 00:17:57,333
You're even holding
each other's hands.

285
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:11,500
No.

286
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:12,633
You're not real.

287
00:18:12,767 --> 00:18:15,933
Go back to your grave
because you're dead!

288
00:18:16,467 --> 00:18:19,600
Are you going to kill me again?

289
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:21,100
Yes, I will.

290
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:24,767
I will do that again and again
just to keep you in the grave!

291
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:28,433
How shocking is that?
You're so afraid of the dead.

292
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:31,200
But what's scarier is that
you're very much alive,

293
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:34,900
yet your heart and mind
are shrouded in darkness.

294
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:37,533
Your sowing of terror is over.

295
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:39,867
Because I'm here.

296
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,100
And I will be the one
to bury you in the grave.

297
00:18:46,067 --> 00:18:47,100
Go ahead and try.

298
00:18:48,267 --> 00:18:49,067
Go!

299
00:18:49,867 --> 00:18:51,067
You're not real.

300
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,833
You're not real!

301
00:18:52,967 --> 00:18:54,700
You're only in my imagination.

302
00:19:00,533 --> 00:19:01,700
Stay away from me.

303
00:19:26,533 --> 00:19:27,433
Pryvaxil?

304
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:31,533
What's your illness, Jade?

305
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:55,000
What happened?

306
00:19:56,467 --> 00:19:57,433
Olive?

307
00:19:58,333 --> 00:19:59,000
Wake up.

308
00:19:59,767 --> 00:20:00,633
Olive.

309
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:02,100
You've been here
for an hour now.

310
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:03,467
What happened?

311
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:05,000
It's so messy.

312
00:20:05,133 --> 00:20:07,533
No! You're not real.

313
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:09,633
- What is it this time?
- No!

314
00:20:11,167 --> 00:20:13,033
- Olive?
- Where is she?

315
00:20:13,167 --> 00:20:15,833
- I knew this would happen.
- I saw Emma.

316
00:20:15,967 --> 00:20:17,467
She came here. She was inside.

317
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:19,167
Olive, you're hallucinating
again!

318
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:20,200
No, I'm not!

319
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:21,233
I saw Emma!

320
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:22,767
- What are you talking about?
- I saw her.

321
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:24,300
I saw Emma.

322
00:20:24,433 --> 00:20:26,033
Stop!

323
00:20:26,167 --> 00:20:27,300
How dare you slap me!

324
00:20:27,433 --> 00:20:30,433
How many times should
I tell you she's dead?

325
00:20:30,567 --> 00:20:31,800
I saw Emma!

326
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:33,667
Olive! Emma's dead!

327
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:34,933
Come on!

328
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:37,467
What's wrong with you?

329
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,633
No.

330
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:41,167
I can still feel her.

331
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,567
Oh my gosh. Olive, that's
enough.

332
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:43,833
I'm sure with what I saw.

333
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:46,100
That's enough, Olive. Stop!

334
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,067
You're getting crazy, Olive.

335
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,500
Please!

336
00:20:50,633 --> 00:20:52,333
Take your medicine.

337
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:15,067
No!

338
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,200
No!

339
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:18,200
This is all in my mind.

340
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:19,900
This is not real.

341
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:21,500
No!

342
00:21:21,633 --> 00:21:23,600
Where is it?

343
00:21:25,667 --> 00:21:27,233
No!

344
00:21:30,633 --> 00:21:33,233
It's just my imagination.
You're not real!

345
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:36,867
You're not real!

346
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:49,233
Hasn't Dra. Samson replied yet
on what the medicine is for?

347
00:21:49,367 --> 00:21:50,667
Not yet.

348
00:21:55,533 --> 00:21:56,233
Why?

349
00:21:58,467 --> 00:21:59,200
Nothing.

350
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:01,900
I'm proud of you.

351
00:22:02,867 --> 00:22:07,233
You did it alone.

352
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:10,333
You don't need me anymore.

353
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:12,100
You can do it on your own.

354
00:22:12,933 --> 00:22:14,600
I still can't, Logan.

355
00:22:15,333 --> 00:22:16,833
I still need you.

356
00:22:16,967 --> 00:22:18,800
I need your help.

357
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:23,800
But I'm happy that you're proud
of me.

358
00:22:24,533 --> 00:22:26,567
And I know you'll be even
prouder of me

359
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:30,667
because I have another idea
on how to haunt Jade.

360
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,333
Wow.

361
00:22:32,467 --> 00:22:33,700
Really?

362
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:35,467
Go ahead.

363
00:22:35,933 --> 00:22:36,500
Tell me.

364
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:40,500
I changed her ringtone.

365
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:51,567
How will you use
that to scare her?

366
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:06,233
Good morning, Ligaya!

367
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,667
Are you saying something?

368
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:11,433
Wait.

369
00:23:14,667 --> 00:23:16,633
What is it? What are you saying?

370
00:23:16,767 --> 00:23:18,000
Please stop.

371
00:23:18,133 --> 00:23:18,733
Stop.

372
00:23:18,867 --> 00:23:21,233
Don't you enjoy this?

373
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:24,133
Let's party, Ligaya!

374
00:23:26,467 --> 00:23:28,200
Mookie!

375
00:23:28,333 --> 00:23:31,867
Danilo!

376
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:36,967
- Mookie! Danilo!
- Mookie! Danilo!

377
00:23:37,100 --> 00:23:39,167
Go ahead and scream.

378
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:41,967
No one can hear you.

379
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:56,433
Flor, I need your help so
I can get even with Jade.

380
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,500
Game!

381
00:23:58,633 --> 00:23:59,700
You know what, Emma?

382
00:23:59,833 --> 00:24:03,067
In a battle, there's something
called disarmament.

383
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:07,633
You first target the opponent's
weapons before you attack.

384
00:24:07,767 --> 00:24:10,833
It might be better if we change
the contents of the bottle.

385
00:24:10,967 --> 00:24:13,367
Zintrixa-X or ZX.

386
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:15,200
We will replace the tablets
with it.

387
00:24:15,333 --> 00:24:18,233
In short, it'll make her crazy.

388
00:24:18,367 --> 00:24:20,400
Mom is here.

389
00:24:20,533 --> 00:24:24,967
I will fill the void left
by Maria Angela in your heart.

390
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:26,633
I will love you.

391
00:24:26,767 --> 00:24:29,000
I will never leave you.

392
00:24:29,167 --> 00:24:31,133
I already know who owns the SUV.

393
00:24:31,267 --> 00:24:33,133
Will I finally see Emma?

394
00:24:33,267 --> 00:24:34,367
Bro, here's the car.

395
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:35,533
Here's the house.

396
00:24:35,667 --> 00:24:37,000
You're the one keeping watch
over our house, right?

397
00:24:37,133 --> 00:24:37,767
Danilo, calm down!

398
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:39,033
Where's Emma?
